types.section:
{{fr-verb}}

# {{lb|fr|transitive}} to [[open]]
# {{lb|fr|transitive}} to [[begin]], to [[initiate]]
#: {{ux|fr|À peine arrivé, il '''a ouvert''' les hostilités.|t=He '''initiated''' hostilities almost as soon as he arrived.}}
# {{lb|fr|reflexive}} to [[open]] (of a [[door]] or a [[flower]])
# {{lb|fr|reflexive}} to [[open]], to [[begin]]
#: {{ux|fr|La séquence s''''ouvre''' sur une scène de nuit.|t=The sequence '''opens''' with a night scene.}}
# to [[turn on]], to [[switch on]], to [[put on]] (of a [[device]] or an [[appliance]])
# to [[open]] it or the [[door]], to [[answer]] it or the [[door]], to [[get]] it
#: {{ux|fr|On sonne à la porte. Je vais '''ouvrir'''.|t=There's someone at the door; I'll '''open/answer/get it'''.}}
#: {{ux|fr|Sophie, '''ouvre'''-moi, je voudrais te parler !|t=Sophie, '''open the door'''; I want to talk to you!}}
#: {{ux|fr|Allez, arrête tes bêtises et va '''ouvrir''' à Patrick ; il doit avoir froid dehors.|t=Stop being silly and '''open the door''' for Patrick; he must be cold outside.}}
# {{lb|fr|reflexive}} to [[cut]] something [[open]], to [[gash]] something (of a part of one's [[body]])
#: {{ux|fr|Le gardien de but a plongé pour rattraper le ballon, s'est cogné contre le poteau et '''s'est ouvert''' l'arcade sourcilière.|t=The goalkeeper dived to catch the ball, banged himself on the goalpost and '''cut''' his eyebrow '''open'''.}}
# {{lb|fr|reflexive}} to [[open]] onto, to [[lead]] into (+ [[sur]])
#: {{ux|fr|Cette porte '''s'ouvre sur''' le jardin.|t=This door '''opens onto''' the garden.}}
# {{lb|fr|intransitive}} to [[open]] onto, to [[overlook]], to [[look]] onto (of a [[door]] or a [[window]]) (+ [[sur]])
#: {{ux|fr|La porte '''ouvre sur''' la rue.|t=The door '''opens onto''' the street.}}
# {{lb|fr|reflexive}} to [[open up]] to, to be [[open]] to, to be [[exposed]] to, to get a [[feel]] for (+ [[à]])
#: {{ux|fr|Sa fille '''s'est ouverte à''' la musique sur le piano familial.|t=The girl '''got a feel for''' music playing her family's piano.}}
# {{lb|fr|reflexive}} to [[open up]] to, to [[confide]] in (+ [[à]])
# to [[make]], to [[create]], to [[open up]] (e.g., a [[path]])

